    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Produce blog drafts with Google Sheets and WordPress 24/7\n\n**Pattern:** Content Generation · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nProduce blog drafts with Google Sheets and WordPress 24/7. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual publishing is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nWeekly Schedule → Required Fields Present? → Frame the Assignment → Coordinator Agent → Unpack Sections → Persist Deliverable to Notion → Load Previous Snapshot → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to content generation without manual effort\n- Anyone automating publishing in content creation\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n- Improves response time\n- Responds in seconds\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Anthropic API key; Google OAuth2 / service account; Notion integration token; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "b978fcfa-63ca-5650-308a-d80d7102ec23",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "62392876-3225-b24d-3511-043d2e80620d",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "842405b9-b5f3-2350-16d5-3e58a357cc14",
      "name": "🤖 AI cluster"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        610,
